      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "FIGHTER COMMAND (7) made a winning return from a six-month spell two back at Melton before being edged out by a smart one last start. Draws wider but won the only time he raced here and should be fit now having recorded three wins and a placing from four previous third-up attempts. BEACH DIAMOND (6) was one of the leading three-year-old fillies of last season and went to the paddock off a string of top-two finishes, highlighted by wins in the Breeders Crown and Vicbred finals. Won her lone try at this distance and is yet to taste defeat in three fresh attempts. She should be ready to fire again off two trial placings. MY ULTIMATE BARNEY (5) added to his consistent form when he came from the back row for fourth in the Riverina Championships final last start. Runner-up from this barrier three back at Melton and races well at this distance. JUSTALITTLESIP NZ (4) has been solid at his last couple and is proven at the distance. First four hope.",
